JOHANNESBURG Both grades of petrol will decrease by 8c a litre on Wednesday, while the price of diesel will down by 2c.However, the newly announced fuel taxes will take effect from April 1, 2017 leaving motorists to pay an extra 39 cents a litre.INFOGRAPHIC: This is what the petrol price hike means to youThe Automobile Association wants the government fuel tax levies reviewed, warning the hike will hit motorists hard.On Wednesday, Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan announced increases to fuel and Road Accident Fund levies in the budget.And Treasury is currently mulling the potential of removing the current zero-VAT rating, on fuel.eNCA